# Super Trading

Read [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) and [docs/project-status.md](../../docs/project-status.md) for full context.

## Architecture (non-negotiable)

- `bots/` (Python) — all trading logic, ML, OANDA, Redis publish
- `backend/` (NestJS) — REST + WebSocket/SSE relay only; never touch OANDA
- `frontend/` (Vite React) — dashboard; consumes API + Socket.IO + SSE
- Redis pub/sub connects Python to Nest; Nest forwards to the frontend

## Before editing

1. Check [docs/project-status.md](../../docs/project-status.md) for what's implemented vs stubbed
2. Keep diffs minimal; match surrounding code style
3. Never commit `.env` or secrets
4. Schema changes → `docker/postgres/init.sql` + `make db-reset` (TypeORM `synchronize` is off)

## Run locally

```bash
make install
make run-trading    # terminal 1: Postgres + Redis + Python bots (:3210 not used)
make run-dashboard  # terminal 2: API :3210 + FE :3211

# Or without bootstrap scripts (after make up):
make dev-api   # :3210
make dev-fe    # :3211
make dev-bots
```

## Pitfalls

- `VITE_WS_URL` must be `http://localhost:3210` (Socket.IO), not `ws://`
- Design doc uses `api/`/`dashboard/` — repo uses `backend/`/`frontend/`
- Design doc Phase 1 checkmarks are targets, not done work — see project-status.md
- Paper trade only until explicitly approved for live
- New bots: JSON in `bots/config/bots/` + register in `bot_registry.py`
